ask: harden auto_bridge netlink + init/exit paths (audit B4)

AUDIT-auto_bridge.md:
- AB-03 netlink_kernel_create() return value was discarded; abm_nl_init
        always returned 0. If allocation failed, abm_nl was NULL and
        every subsequent abm_nl_send() / netlink_kernel_release() would
        NULL-deref. Now checked; abm_nl_init returns -ENOMEM on failure.
- AB-04 abm_init() failure paths leaked all prior init steps. Each
        sub-init was followed by an unconditional `return rc` with no
        unwind of (workqueue, l2flow_table, brevent cb, netlink, proc,
        sysctl, nf hooks) acquired earlier. Replaced with sequential
        gotos that unwind in reverse order.
- AB-05 abm_l2flow_table_init() returned -ENOMEM after creating
        l2flow_cache if brroute_cache failed, leaking l2flow_cache.
        Destroy l2flow_cache on the brroute_cache failure path.
- AB-06 abm_exit() never called abm_sysctl_fini(), leaking the
        registered pernet_subsys; on rmmod+modprobe cycle this is
        unregister-twice and a use-after-free of abm_net_ops. Added
        the missing call. (Also drops the __maybe_unused tag since the
        function is now used.)

Behaviour-preserving on success paths. AB-03/AB-04/AB-06 are
load-fail / unload-leak defences; AB-05 is an OOM-leak fix.

Signed-off-by: ASK audit B4
